==English==

===Etymology===
Of [[German]] origin, introduced to [[Britain]] by the [[Normans]]. Original form and meaning is disputed - possible variant of [[Godfrey]], but most likely that several similar names have fallen together.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Jeffrey]] (the usual spelling in the [[US]])

===Proper noun===
'''Geoffrey'''

# A [[male]] [[given name]].

